cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with privacy concerns related to location-based data, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories. The paper proposes differentially private schemes for publishing aggregated mobility data, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the moving characteristics of mobile users, which is related to the spatial information (cs.SI) sub-category.
